That reminds me of a couple of years ago, I took my '75 Westy to pick up my daughter from cheerleading practice. There was another dad there picking up his daughter in a brand new $200K Ferrari. Nobody gave the Ferrari a second look, I don't think anybody even realized what it was, but when I rolled in in the Westy, the crowd went nuts! The Ferrari guy and I are now friends (he started out with Porsche 914's) and he invites me and the Westy to a private car show each year that he holds on his property.    Jeff
